[size=5][b]Toggle Turn-Based In Combat[/b][/size]

A Pillars of Eternity 1 mod that lets you switch between [b]real-time-with-pause[/b] and [b]turn-based ("Tactical") combat[/b] at runtime, from a keybind — [b]including mid-combat, both directions.[/b]

The base game ships both combat modes, but locks the choice in the options menu: the checkbox greys out once you're in a session or in a fight. That lock is UI-only — the underlying mode is a single live setting, so this mod just flips it whenever you want.

[size=4][b]What works[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][b]turn-based → real-time[/b] — any time, including mid-combat.
[*][b]real-time → turn-based[/b] — out of combat.
[*][b]real-time → turn-based, mid-combat[/b] — the current fighters enroll into the turn order the next frame.
[/list]

Turning turn-based on mid-fight rides the game's own combat loop: every combatant self-enrolls into the turn system exactly as if the fight had started that way. Turning it back off clears the turn queue and real-time resumes. Your chosen mode saves with your game.

[size=4][b]The keybind is the game's own (default: T)[/b][/size]

This mod doesn't add its own hotkey UI. Pillars already ships a first-class control for this — Obsidian wired it up but left it dormant, with nothing polling it. This mod simply consumes it, so:
[list]
[*][b]Default key is T[/b] (the game's own default). Rebind it in [b]Options → Controls[/b] (the camera/turn group, near [i]Pass Turn[/i] / [i]Wait Turn[/i]) like any other control — with real conflict detection and persistence.
[*]It works everywhere, [b]including in combat[/b].
[*]The center-bottom HUD toggle button (which normally fades out during a fight) is kept visible and clickable too.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Install[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*]Close Pillars of Eternity.
[*]Download the zip and extract it anywhere.
[*]Double-click [b]install.bat[/b]. It auto-detects your install; if it can't find one, it asks you to paste the game folder — quotes are optional, and paths with spaces or parentheses are fine.
[*]Launch the game and press [b]T[/b] in combat.
[/list]

Needs only Windows PowerShell (built into Windows) — no .NET SDK or compiler.

[size=4][b]Uninstall[/b][/size]

Double-click [b]uninstall.bat[/b]. It surgically removes [b]only[/b] this mod's hook and DLL — any other mods that patch the same method are left intact.

[size=4][b]Notes[/b][/size]
[list]
[*]Sidecar DLL; [b]no game data files are edited[/b]. No Harmony or other runtime dependencies — the only bundled file is Mono.Cecil, used once by the installer to inject the hook.
[*]A one-time backup of Assembly-CSharp.dll is made next to it.
[*]Steam "Verify integrity of game files" will revert the hook; just re-run the installer if that happens.
[*]Coexists with other mods that hook the same method.
[/list]

[size=4][b]Source[/b][/size]

MIT licensed. Contains only original mod code; no Obsidian game assets.
